rComments: So Dr. Lee is supposed to be the TMM director but apparently other professors seem to hold/give more to the program than him. The program is fairly small and it is very easy to get your students' feedback and act upon them- instead, he does not seem to care much. Teaching: His grading criteria is very subjective and unrealistic (high expectations!)
I truly loved Dr. Lee, really fair exams loves his pathways. If you take this course focus only on pathways.

I think everyone was little caught off guard when he didn't have lecture summaries like the other profs and his slides were empty, but I thought he was pretty good. Explained everything really well, you just have to write down EVERYTHING he says. His questions weren't too bad and the material he taught was interesting. Do his assigned readings!
Is a good lecturer. Not available to help outside of class hours. He's pretty good overall but his exam questions can be ambiguous. Was overshadowed by the amazingness that is Dr. Ekker
Mean person. Loved pushing the mac computers.  Seems really caught up in his own research and himself and doesn't really seem to enjoy teaching.

Bad lecture notes...just copies and pastes pictures from the textbook. Very unfriendly person. Questions on exams are very unclear often. Told us our midterm would be very easy and it was probably the hardest one I've ever had. He is far too focused on his research and doesn't seem to care for teaching.
good prof, good notes, but a bad person
Notes are terrible. Midterm questions are ambigious. But he was very fair and taught the class at an appropriate level. Just pay attention in class.
